
[1]contrite

   CONTRITE, a. [L., to break or bruise; to rub or wear. See Trite.]
   Literally, worn or bruised. Hence, broken-hearted for sin; deeply
   affected with grief and sorrow for having offended God; humble;
   penitent; as a contrite sinner.

   A broken and a contrite heart, O God, thou wilt not despise. Psalm 51.
